description:
Martyrdom & The Fifth Seal In The Book Of Revelation | Questions & Answers

1. After which event in the life of Jesus, and in what year did He begin to loose the 1st seal?
A. After His death & ascension in AD 31
B. After His baptism & anointing in AD 27
C. After his birth in 4 BCD. After His final cleansing of the earthly temple in AD 31

2. What date was the second seal opened?
A. A.D. 27
B. A.D. 31
C. A.D. 34
D. A.D. 64

3. What date and time period was the third seal opened?
A. A.D. 313 to 321
B. A.D. 538 to 1798
C. A.D. 1798 to 1844
D. A.D. 27 to 34

4. What year was the opening of the fourth seal?
A. 321
B. 457
C. 538
D. 508

5. What date was the fifth seal opened?
A. 1755
B. 1773
C. 1780
D. 1798

6. Under the fifth seal, the slain souls were revealed under the altar. What does this altar represent contextually?
A. Altar inside church
B. Altar of sacrifice in the court
C. An altar in heaven
D. Martyred by fire

7. The souls that were slain cried out to God. Whose life in the Bible was used as an example of personification?
A. John the Baptist
B. Stephen
C. Abel
D. Jesus

8.  Which of the following scriptures does not confirm that the dead is unconscious?
A. Ecclesiastes 9:5
B. 2 Corinthians 5:8
C. Psalm 146:4
D. Isaiah 38:18,19


9. What is that spirit that returns to God when a person dies in Ecclesiastes 12:7?
A. Soul
B. Breath
C. The persons mind
D. The persons personality

10. What comprises a living soul according to the Bible?
A. Mind and body
B. Mind and spirit
C. Breath and spirit
D. Breath and body

11. The slain souls were given white robes? What does that mean?
A. Dressed in white for burial
B. They wore white to their execution
C. Killers mockingly dressed them in white
D. Jesus declared them righteous

12. The saints rest in the graves until the remnant are martyred similarly. During which event does martyrdom cease?
A. Civil War
B. Mark of the Beast
C. Stripping Away Liberties
D. Seven last plagues
